reviewText: Don'tcha hate hearing the words "Yes!! But..."?Briefly: The BEST Ozzie and Harriet Collection is the100 episode 12-disc MILL CREEK one for about the sameprice as this one.That said...the FIFTEEN episodes on THIS collection,from seasons 1,2,6,8,9,10,11,12,& 14 that are=> NOT <=on the [other] 100-episode collection ARE worth theasking price for THIS one.For the money, you'd rather have the extra five minutes onepisodes than a commentary by the, now deceased, Davidspeaking with his nephew on plot developments that ARE re-vealed ON the so-call bootleg, public-domain, non-estateauthorized 100 episode, 12-DVD collection.Right?The NINE episodes, here, that are a-l-s-o on the LARGER col-lection have as much as 5-minutes--each--cut out of them.What a shame that some episodes are forever gone... unlessyou buy some of those OTHER ones saved by someone with theirOWN 16mm film collections, as collected by MILL CREEK!The DIFFERENT episodes on THIS collection are between 23 and26-minutes, and the last few are even in the original color.So, again, the OTHER 100-episode collection is more complete--although the audio and video sucks (a bit) the episodes AREcomplete with commercials, in most cases--Coca-Cola and KodakCamera-- and have as much as an extra FIVE (5!) minutes an ep-isode... and a few vintage commercials as well.BTW: in the olden days, some shows used a process-- to allowfor another two commercials (without scissors) by S-L-I-G-H-T-L-Yspeeding up the shows in syndication (reruns). The very slightlyhigher speaking voices were best percieved when you heard music...not a slightly higher pitched "Hey Aaaabbbbbot!"The speed was re-adjusted on the ABBOTT AND COSTELLO SHOW,and not a minute of those shows are gone.Let's hope that there ARE un-cut episodes of OZZIE AND HARRIETout there...somewhere.Yes!! But...I wouldn't hold my breath!

reviewText: The adventures of Ozzie & Harriet: best of Ricky & Dave. This boxed set compared to the previous is probably the best in quality so far. The black and white episodes are very good and clear, their is various episodes from the 14 year run including two beautiful color episodes. This box set is worth buying for the color episodes alone. I only wish they would add more color episodes. shoutfactory has done a very job in this box set. If your buying your first ozzie & harriet box set get this one.
summary: THE BEST IN THE COLLECTION OF OZZIE& HARRIET

reviewText: If you wish to know about true family role playing at its best, grab anything about the Nelsons.  It had to be hard to be one of the first family to be filmed for TV.  The family had its moments and its glories.  I truly think there will not be another one like the family of Nelsons.
